    print "\n---------\nNote: file_play_record makes no sound."
    print "It plays sound from a fileplay ugen as input to a filerec ugen."
    print "The result is a copy from testinput.wav (if it exists) to"
    print "testoutput.wav. You have to play it yourself (it just a test)."
    print "----------\n"
    // Note: if you allow the File_play_record() to be GC'd, there will be
    // no handler for "fply.atend(FINISH, this)" and frec will record
    // forever. It seems like you could direct .atend() to send .stop() to
    // frec, but this does not work either: Actions only maintain weak
    // references to action targets to avoid a circular reference problem
    // (object ref counts never go to zero so they never terminate and send
    // a termination action, so the ref count never goes to zero, ...).
    file_play_record_inst = File_play_record()


